HEADWORD: Boothose
<hw>Boot"hose`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Stocking hose, or spatterdashes, in lieu of boots.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hose made to be worn with boots, as by travelers on
horseback.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boothy</ent>⟦br⟧
